ciscoIkeFlowMIB.name: ciscoIkeFlowMIB
ciscoIkeFlowMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-ipsecmib@external.cisco.com
ciscoIkeFlowMIB.description: This is a MIB module for monitoring the structures and status of IPsec control flows based on Internet Key Exchange protocol. The MIB models standard aspects of the IKE protocol. Synopsis This MIB module models status, performance and failures of the IKEv1- and IKEv2-based signaling in IPsec, FC-SP(and similar) protocols. In practice, the security protocols such as IPsec, FC-SP and CTS use a signaling protocol such as IKE, KINK, or some such. A number of characteristics of these signaling protocols are generic. The generic attributes and status of signaling activity has been modeled in CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB. This MIB module augments CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB with IKE-specific MIB objects. (Signaling protocols are also referred to this document as 'Control Protocols', since they perform session control.) History of the MIB A precursor to this MIB was written by Tivoli and implemented in IBM Nways routers in 1999. That MIB instrumented both IKE(v1) and IPsec in a single module. During late 1999, Cisco adopted the MIB and together with Tivoli published the IPsec Flow Monitor MIB in IETF IPsec WG in draft-ietf-ipsec-flow-monitoring-mib-00.txt. In 2000, the MIB was Cisco-ized and implemented this draft as CISCO-IPSEC-FLOW-MONITOR-MIB in IOS and VPN3000 platforms. With the evolution of IKEv2, the MIB was modified and presented to the IPsec WG again in May 2003 in draft-ietf-ipsec-flow-monitoring-mib-02.txt. This version of the draft is a Cisco-ized version that culls out the IKE-specific aspects of the IPsec Flow Monitor MIB. Overview of MIB The MIB contains five major groups of objects which are used to manage the IKE protocol activity. These groups include the global statistics, IKE tunnel table, IKE History Group and a notification Group. The tunnel table and the history table have a sparse-table relationship with the corresponding tables in the CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB (details in the DESCRIPTION of the respective tables). Acronyms The following acronyms are used in this document: Flow, Tunnel: An ISAKMP SA can be regarded as representing a flow of ISAKMP/IKE traffic. Hence an ISAKMP is referred to as a 'Phase 1 Tunnel' in this document. IPsec: Secure IP Protocol ISAKMP: Internet Security Association and Key Management Protocol IKE: Internet Key Exchange Protocol MM: Main Mode - the process of setting up a Phase 1 SA to secure the exchanges required to setup Phase 2 SAs Phase 2 Tunnel: AN instance of a non-ISAKMP SA bundle in which all the SA share the same proxy identifiers (IDii,IDir) protect the same stream of application traffic. Such an SA bundle is termed a 'Phase 2 Tunnel'. Note that a Phase 2 tunnel may comprise different SA bundles and different number of SA bundles at different times (due to key refresh). QM: Quick Mode - the process of setting up Phase 2 Security Associations using a Phase 1 SA. SA: Security Association (ref: rfc2408). VPN: Virtual Private Network.

cifIkeGlobalStatsTable.name: cifIkeGlobalStatsTable
cifIkeGlobalStatsTable.description: The Phase-1 IKE Global Statistics Table. There is one entry in this table for each Phase-1 IKE, protocol('cpIkev1' and 'cpIkev2') implemented by the managed entity. For all the counter objects in the table below, initially when the IKE Tunnel becomes active and appears in this table, they would contain a value of zero.

cifIkeGlobalStatsEntry.name: cifIkeGlobalStatsEntry
cifIkeGlobalStatsEntry.description: Each entry contains the global statistics pertaining to the specific IKE protocol.

cifIkeGlobalInP2Exchgs.name: cifIkeGlobalInP2Exchgs
cifIkeGlobalInP2Exchgs.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges received by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Tunnels.

cifIkeGlobalInP2ExchgInvalids.name: cifIkeGlobalInP2ExchgInvalids
cifIkeGlobalInP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges which were received and found to be invalid by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Tunnels.

cifIkeGlobalInP2ExchgRejects.name: cifIkeGlobalInP2ExchgRejects
cifIkeGlobalInP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges which were received and rejected by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Tunnels.

cifIkeGlobalOutP2Exchgs.name: cifIkeGlobalOutP2Exchgs
cifIkeGlobalOutP2Exchgs.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges which were sent by all currently and previously active IPsec Phase-1 Tunnels.

cifIkeGlobalOutP2ExchgInvalids.name: cifIkeGlobalOutP2ExchgInvalids
cifIkeGlobalOutP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges which were sent and found to be invalid by all currently and previously active Phase-1 Tunnels.

cifIkeGlobalOutP2ExchgRejects.name: cifIkeGlobalOutP2ExchgRejects
cifIkeGlobalOutP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges which were sent and rejected by all currently and previously active Phase-1 IKE Tunnels.

cifIkeGlobalInXauths.name: cifIkeGlobalInXauths
cifIkeGlobalInXauths.description: The number of times the extended authentication requests was received by the managed entity from a peer.

cifIkeGlobalInXauthFailures.name: cifIkeGlobalInXauthFailures
cifIkeGlobalInXauthFailures.description: The number of times the extended authentication information supplied by an IKE peer was found to be invalid by the local entity.

cifIkeGlobalOutXauthFailures.name: cifIkeGlobalOutXauthFailures
cifIkeGlobalOutXauthFailures.description: The number of times the extended authentication information supplied by the managed entity to an IKE peer was found to be invalid by the remote peer.

cifIkeGlobalInNewGrpReqs.name: cifIkeGlobalInNewGrpReqs
cifIkeGlobalInNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely.

cifIkeGlobalOutNewGrpReqs.name: cifIkeGlobalOutNewGrpReqs
cifIkeGlobalOutNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally.

cifIkeGlobalInNewGrpRejectReqs.name: cifIkeGlobalInNewGrpRejectReqs
cifIkeGlobalInNewGrpRejectReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely that ended in reject.

cifIkeGlobalOutNewGrpRejectReqs.name: cifIkeGlobalOutNewGrpRejectReqs
cifIkeGlobalOutNewGrpRejectReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally that ended in reject.

cifIkeTunnelTable.name: cifIkeTunnelTable
cifIkeTunnelTable.description: The Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Tunnel Table. There is one entry in this table for each active IPsec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunnelEntry.name: cifIkeTunnelEntry
cifIkeTunnelEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with an active Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. The rows in this table correspond 1-to-1 with a subset of the rows in cisgIpsSgTunnelTable, specifically the subset which represent Phase-1 IKE Tunnels. Hence, the value of the index 'cisgIpsSgProtocol' in this table is always 'cpIkev1' or 'cpIkev2'. For all the counter objects in the table below, initially when the Phase-1 IKE Tunnel becomes active and appears in this table, they would contain a value of zero.

cifIkeTunNegoMode.name: cifIkeTunNegoMode
cifIkeTunNegoMode.description: The negotiation mode of the Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunDHGrp.name: cifIkeTunDHGrp
cifIkeTunDHGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

cifIkeTunSaRefreshThreshold.name: cifIkeTunSaRefreshThreshold
cifIkeTunSaRefreshThreshold.description: The security association refresh threshold in seconds. If the tunnel does not refresh its security associations, the value of this MIB object is zero.

cifIkeTunTotalRefreshes.name: cifIkeTunTotalRefreshes
cifIkeTunTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security associations refreshes performed. If the tunnel does not refresh its security associations, the value of this MIB object is never incremented.

cifIkeTunInP2Exchgs.name: cifIkeTunInP2Exchgs
cifIkeTunInP2Exchgs.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges received by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunInP2ExchgInvalids.name: cifIkeTunInP2ExchgInvalids
cifIkeTunInP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges received and found to be invalid by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunInP2ExchgRejects.name: cifIkeTunInP2ExchgRejects
cifIkeTunInP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges received and rejected by this Phase-1 Tunnel.

cifIkeTunInP2SaDelRequests.name: cifIkeTunInP2SaDelRequests
cifIkeTunInP2SaDelRequests.description: The total number of Phase-2 security association delete requests received by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunOutP2Exchgs.name: cifIkeTunOutP2Exchgs
cifIkeTunOutP2Exchgs.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges sent by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunOutP2ExchgInvalids.name: cifIkeTunOutP2ExchgInvalids
cifIkeTunOutP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges sent and found to be invalid by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunOutP2ExchgRejects.name: cifIkeTunOutP2ExchgRejects
cifIkeTunOutP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges sent and rejected by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunInNewGrpReqs.name: cifIkeTunInNewGrpReqs
cifIkeTunInNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely using this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunOutNewGrpReqs.name: cifIkeTunOutNewGrpReqs
cifIkeTunOutNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally using this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunInNewGrpRejectedReqs.name: cifIkeTunInNewGrpRejectedReqs
cifIkeTunInNewGrpRejectedReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely using this IKE tunnel that ended in reject.

cifIkeTunOutNewGrpRejectedReqs.name: cifIkeTunOutNewGrpRejectedReqs
cifIkeTunOutNewGrpRejectedReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally using this IKE tunnel that ended in reject.

cifIkeTunInConfigs.name: cifIkeTunInConfigs
cifIkeTunInConfigs.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings received (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) by the local entity on the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunOutConfigs.name: cifIkeTunOutConfigs
cifIkeTunOutConfigs.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings dispatched (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) by the local entity on the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunInConfigRejects.name: cifIkeTunInConfigRejects
cifIkeTunInConfigRejects.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings which were received (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) and rejected by this entity using the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunOutConfigRejects.name: cifIkeTunOutConfigRejects
cifIkeTunOutConfigRejects.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings which were dispatched (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) by this entity and were rejected by the peer (client) using the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunnelHistTable.name: cifIkeTunnelHistTable
cifIkeTunnelHistTable.description: The Phase-1 Internet Key Exchange Tunnel history table. This table is conceptually a sliding window in which only the last 'N' entries are maintained, where 'N' is the value of the object 'cisgIpsSgHistTableSize' (defined in defined in CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB). If the value of 'cisgIpsSgHistTableSize' is 0, then this table will be empty. For all the counter objects in the table below, initially when the Tunnel entry appears in this table, they would contain a value of zero.

cifIkeTunnelHistEntry.name: cifIkeTunnelHistEntry
cifIkeTunnelHistEntry.description: Each entry contains the attributes associated with a previously active Phase-1 IKE Tunnel. This table has a sparse table relationship with the generic Phase-1 Tunnel history table 'cisgIpsSgTunnelHistTable' defined in CISCO-IPSEC-SIGNALING-MIB. However, the value of the index column in this table will always be either 'cpIkev1' or 'cpIkev2'.

cifIkeTunHistNegoMode.name: cifIkeTunHistNegoMode
cifIkeTunHistNegoMode.description: The negotiation mode of the Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistDHGrp.name: cifIkeTunHistDHGrp
cifIkeTunHistDHGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in Phase-1 IKE negotiations.

cifIkeTunHistTotalRefreshes.name: cifIkeTunHistTotalRefreshes
cifIkeTunHistTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security associations refreshes performed.

cifIkeTunHistTotalSas.name: cifIkeTunHistTotalSas
cifIkeTunHistTotalSas.description: The total number of security associations used during the life of the Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistInP2Exchgs.name: cifIkeTunHistInP2Exchgs
cifIkeTunHistInP2Exchgs.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges received by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistInP2ExchgInvalids.name: cifIkeTunHistInP2ExchgInvalids
cifIkeTunHistInP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges received on this tunnel that were found to contain references to unrecognized security parameters.

cifIkeTunHistInP2ExchgRejects.name: cifIkeTunHistInP2ExchgRejects
cifIkeTunHistInP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges received on this tunnel that were validated but were rejected by the local policy.

cifIkeTunHistOutP2Exchgs.name: cifIkeTunHistOutP2Exchgs
cifIkeTunHistOutP2Exchgs.description: The total number of Phase-2 security association delete requests received by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistOutP2ExchgInvalids.name: cifIkeTunHistOutP2ExchgInvalids
cifIkeTunHistOutP2ExchgInvalids.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges sent by this Phase-1 IKE Tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistOutP2ExchgRejects.name: cifIkeTunHistOutP2ExchgRejects
cifIkeTunHistOutP2ExchgRejects.description: The total number of Phase-2 exchanges sent on this tunnel that were rejected by the peer, because it contained references to security parameters not recognized by the peer.

cifIkeTunHistInNewGrpReqs.name: cifIkeTunHistInNewGrpReqs
cifIkeTunHistInNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime.

cifIkeTunHistOutNewGrpReqs.name: cifIkeTunHistOutNewGrpReqs
cifIkeTunHistOutNewGrpReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime.

cifIkeTunHistInNewGrpRejectReqs.name: cifIkeTunHistInNewGrpRejectReqs
cifIkeTunHistInNewGrpRejectReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated remotely using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime that ended in reject.

cifIkeTunHistOutNewGrpRejectReqs.name: cifIkeTunHistOutNewGrpRejectReqs
cifIkeTunHistOutNewGrpRejectReqs.description: The total number of New Group exchanges initiated locally using this IKE tunnel during its lifetime that ended in reject.

cifIkeTunHistInConfigs.name: cifIkeTunHistInConfigs
cifIkeTunHistInConfigs.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings received (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) by the local entity on the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistOutConfigs.name: cifIkeTunHistOutConfigs
cifIkeTunHistOutConfigs.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings dispatched (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) by the local entity on the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistInConfigsRejects.name: cifIkeTunHistInConfigsRejects
cifIkeTunHistInConfigsRejects.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings which were received (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) and rejected by this entity using the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeTunHistOutConfigsRejects.name: cifIkeTunHistOutConfigsRejects
cifIkeTunHistOutConfigsRejects.description: The total number of Mode Configuration settings which were dispatched (either CFG_REPLY or CFG_SET payloads) by this entity and were rejected by the peer (client) using the ISAKMP SA represented by this IKE tunnel.

cifIkeNotifCntlInNewGrpRejected.name: cifIkeNotifCntlInNewGrpRejected
cifIkeNotifCntlInNewGrpRejected.description: The generation of the 'ciscoIkeFlowInNewGrpRejected' notification is enabled if and only if this object has the value 'true'.

cifIkeNotifCntlOutNewGrpRejected.name: cifIkeNotifCntlOutNewGrpRejected
cifIkeNotifCntlOutNewGrpRejected.description: The generation of the 'ciscoIkeFlowOutNewGrpRejected' notification is enabled if and only if this object has the value 'true'.

ciscoIkeFlowInNewGrpRejected.name: ciscoIkeFlowInNewGrpRejected
ciscoIkeFlowInNewGrpRejected.description: This notification is generated when the managed entity receives and rejects an incoming new group proposal from an IKE peer identified by 'cisgIpsSgFailRemoteAddress'. 'cisgIpsSgFailLocalAddress' identifies the address of the local peer. The ISAKMP context of the exchange can be obtained from the IKE tunnel index which is contained in the index of the varbind objects of this trap.

ciscoIkeFlowOutNewGrpRejected.name: ciscoIkeFlowOutNewGrpRejected
ciscoIkeFlowOutNewGrpRejected.description: This notification is generated when the managed entity issues a new group proposal to the remote peer identified by 'cisgIpsSgFailRemoteAddress' and the peer rejects the proposal. 'cisgIpsSgFailLocalAddress' identifies the address of the local peer. The ISAKMP context of the exchange can be obtained from the IKE tunnel index which is contained in the index of the varbind objects of this trap.

ciscoIkeFlowMIBCompliance.name: ciscoIkeFlowMIBCompliance
ciscoIkeFlowMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities implementing this MIB.

ciscoIkeFlowActivityGroup.name: ciscoIkeFlowActivityGroup
ciscoIkeFlowActivityGroup.description: This group consists of objects that track the current IKE protocol activity: 1) IKE Global Objects 2) IKE Tunnel table.

cifIkeFlowNewGroupGroup.name: cifIkeFlowNewGroupGroup
cifIkeFlowNewGroupGroup.description: This group consists of: 1) Global metrics about new group negotiations 2) IKE Tunnel-wise new group metrics

cifIkeFlowXauthGroup.name: cifIkeFlowXauthGroup
cifIkeFlowXauthGroup.description: This group consists of metrics pertaining to IKE extended authentication. Devices that do not support Xauth need not implement this group.

cifIkeFlowModeConfigGroup.name: cifIkeFlowModeConfigGroup
cifIkeFlowModeConfigGroup.description: This group consists of metrics pertaining to IKE extended authentication. Devices that do not support Xauth need not implement this group.

cifIkeFlowHistoryGroup.name: cifIkeFlowHistoryGroup
cifIkeFlowHistoryGroup.description: This group consists of the core (mandatory) objects pertaining to maintaining history of Internet Key Exchange protocol activity.

cifIkeFlowNewGroupHistoryGroup.name: cifIkeFlowNewGroupHistoryGroup
cifIkeFlowNewGroupHistoryGroup.description: This group consists of archive of new group activity pertaining to expired IKE Phase-1 tunnels.

cifIkeFlowModeConfigHistoryGroup.name: cifIkeFlowModeConfigHistoryGroup
cifIkeFlowModeConfigHistoryGroup.description: This group consists of archive of mode config activity pertaining to expired IKE Phase-1 Tunnels.

cifIkeFlowNotifCntlGroup.name: cifIkeFlowNotifCntlGroup
cifIkeFlowNotifCntlGroup.description: This group of objects controls the sending of notifications pertaining to Phase-1 IKE operations.

cifIkeFlowNotificationGroup.name: cifIkeFlowNotificationGroup
cifIkeFlowNotificationGroup.description: This group contains the notifications pertaining to Phase-1 IKE operations.
